\title{The \code{datatype} command}
\import{shiki-macros}
\put\shiki/language{Isabelle Theory}
\p{The \code{datatype} defines a new type (like \code{typedecl}) but also defines some special constants, called \em{constructors}, which make values of that type. Constructors may optionally take arguments, and these data types may be recursive. }
\shiki{datatype type_name = Constructor1 "arg_type1" "arg_type2" (* ... *)
                   | Constructor2 (* ... *)
                   (* ... *)
}
\p{These datatypes are analogous to the algebraic data types found in many functional programming languages.}